  "notes": "Gallo-Italic Vulgar Latin (~3rd-8th c. CE). Spoken Latin of the Po Valley and NW Italy (Gallia Cisalpina). Key innovations: (1) /u/ -> /y/ fronting. (2) Degemination. (3) Stronger lenition. (4) Final vowel loss/reduction. (5) Nasal vowels. The La Spezia-Rimini line marks the boundary. Ancestor of Piedmontese, Lombard, Ligurian, Emilian-Romagnol (Hull 1982, Pellegrini 1975).",
